Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
checkFiller(25.10)                                          checkFiller(25.10)

Name
       checkFiller - Checks for locations that are missing filler cells, after
       adding the cells with the addFiller command

Syntax
       checkFiller

       [-help]

       [-area <llx lly urx ury>]

       [-file <fileName>]

       [-horizontal_max_length]

       [-powerDomain <power_domain_name>]

       [-vertical_stack_max_length]

       [-reportGap <microns>| -adjacentFiller1]

       Checks  for  locations  that are missing filler cells, after adding the
       cells with the addFiller command. Optionally, generates a  report  with
       details on sites that are missing filler cells. It also does the static
       check, and reports the CPODE Group Spacing violation if the distance of
       the  two  CPODE  groups  is  less  than $value. The distance of the two
       groups should be greater than or equal to $value.

       If you run this command without any parameters, it  reports  the  total
       number of sites in the core area that are missing filler cells.

Parameters
       -adjacentFiller1
              Checks  for  locations  that  are filled with adjacent one-site-
              width fillers. With this parameter, checkFiller flags  any  one-
              site-width filler placed next to each other as a violation.

              To  enable  this  parameter,  you must first specify a one-site-
              width filler by using the following command:

              setFillerMode -core <fillerCellList>

       -area {<llx lly urx ury>}
              Specifies a bounding box for the area  in  which  to  check  for
              missing filler cells.

              Default: Entire core area

       -file <fileName>
              Writes  the  output  of the checkFiller command to the specified
              file.

       -horizontal_max_length
              Checks if the horizontal stack length violates max limit.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each checkFiller parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man  checkFiller.

       -powerDomain <power_domain_name>
              Checks for missing filler cells in the specified power domain.

              The  software  checks  for missing filler cells in all power do-
              mains if you do not specify this parameter.

       -reportGap <microns>
              Checks only for gaps of the specified  size--ignores  any  other
              gap, whether larger or smaller.

       -vertical_stack_max_length
              Checks if the vertical stack length violates the max limit.

Examples
       The  following  command  checks  the  entire  core  area  after running
       addFiller and reports the number  of  sites  that  are  missing  filler
       cells:

       checkFiller

       The software reports the following:

       *INFO: Total number of gaps found: 85

       The following command checks within the specified bounding box at coor-
       dinates  {0  0 100 100} and reports the number of sites that have a gap
       of exactly 0.14 microns:

       checkFiller -reportGap 0.14 -area {0 0 100 100}

       The software reports the following:

       *INFO: Total number of 0.140 microns width gap found: 3

